<td class="newsbody">
	
	<table cellpadding='10' cellspacing='0' border='0' width='100%' align='center'>
	<tr>
	<td valign='top'>WOLF Law:<br /><br />
<br /><br />
Our Laws are simple, and enforced without quarter. Obey them and be welcome members of WOLF. Disobey, and be cast out as mongrels.<br /><br />
<br /><br />
 <br /><br />
<br /><br />
1. Above all, protect the children of Tunare. In game terms, this means that in no way does a member of WOLF attack a wolf, bear, or treant. Many people ask why this protection does not carry on to other animals, and the answer is simple. Any animals that do not con 'amiable' or above, do not call us kin, and are therefore free game. Also, if at any time you see another player attacking a wolf or a bear, you would do well to try and help the animal. As of yet, we're not certain that 'healing' spells effect these animals. However, if you cast 'panic animal' and then zone, the animal will run away from it's attacker. Usually, the attacker is so befuddled at what you've done, they won't run after it. You need to zone (or camp quickly), however, because if you don't the confused child of Tunare will turn on you.<br /><br />
<br /><br />
2. MONGRELS. Mongrels are the lowest form of life to members of WOLF. There are several ways someone can be branded a mongrel, all of which are defined on our Mongrels page, which is currently under construction. Only officers can declare any player a mongrel, but with proof, you can submit your case and the officers of WOLF will decide the Mongrel's fate.<br /><br />
<br /><br />
3. Members of WOLF are a pack. In game terms, this does NOT mean you MUST group with other members of WOLF. However, when another member is in danger and you can help, you are expected to do so. Remember, this is also for your beneifit.<br /><br />
<br /><br />
4. Members of WOLF are to hold their heads high in pride. In game terms, this means no begging for plat or items in shouts. Wolves don't beg, they hunt. If you don't like it, become a mongrel. However, if you are in dire straights, ask another member of WOLF. We DO help our own kind.<br /><br />
<br /><br />
5. Members of WOLF are ALWAYS members of WOLF. In game terms, this means that if you are a member of WOLF you are a role-player. You are to act in character at all times. This does not mean that you may not do /ooc commands... we like to see jokes float across OOC as much as anyone else. We do NOT however, appreciate private conversations over /shout or /ooc. If you have something to say to someone specific, use /tell.<br /><br />
<br /><br />
6. Members of WOLF are pure of thought, we are not gutter-strays. In game terms, and I cannot stress this enough, we do NOT USE profanity in open talk. If we see profanity (even with filters turned on or off) over an /auction, /shout, or /ooc... you will be punished. Too much of this will cause you to be stripped of your WOLF status.<br /><br />
<br /><br />
7. Members of WOLF are their own hunters. In game terms, this means ABSOLUTELY no kill-stealing. We know it's difficult sometimes, especially in newbie areas where two people might be casting on the same kill at the same time. However, if we EVER see blatant kill-stealing, you will be removed from WOLF and be branded a mongrel for the rest of your EQ-life.<br /><br />
<br /><br />
8. Members of WOLF are always happy to help our young. Unlike other guilds, WOLF is happy to accept newbies into our guild, providing you can follow our charter. In order to join WOLF, you must spend a session of EQ with one of our officers, during which we will show you what we know of the game and give you a helping hand. If you have any questions, of course, feel free to ask. WOLF is dedicated to making sure that all players get a good start in EQ.<br /><br />
<br /><br />
9. The officers of WOLF are proud of WOLF, and all of it's members. We want all fo our members to excel, and we will provide as much help as is necessary, while still keeping within the spirit of the game. To this end, we have armor and weapons (tattered leather and rusty) which we will loan out to our younger members. Please keep in mind that this is a LOAN only. We expect you to return it without too much delay. When you 'borrow' the armor or weapons, your name goes on a list (please note only officers will loan out official WOLF armor.) If, by level 7, you do not return the armor or weapons, we will ask for it back. If you dare to disband from WOLF and keep the armor (Come on, it's tattered leather people ;) ) you will be branded as a mongrel.<br /><br />
<br /><br />
The passcode: By my honor, by my soul, I will protect Tunare's children and the forrests of Norrath.<br /><br />
<br /><br />
</td>
